headlines.description: — Collin Sexton had 22 points, Keyonte George scored 12 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter and the Utah Jazz beat Miami 117-109 on Saturday to end the Heat's winning streak at four.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 22 points, George has big 4th in Jazz's 117-109 win over Heat

headlines.description: — The Detroit Pistons ended their NBA record-tying losing streak at 28 games with a 129-127 victory over the short-handed Toronto Raptors on Saturday night, as Cade Cunningham had 30 points and 12 assists.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons beat Raptors 129-127 to end NBA record-tying losing streak at 28 games

events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 22 points and tied a franchise record with 23 assists, becoming only the third player in NBA history with consecutive 20-20 games in those categories, and the Indiana Pacers beat the New York Knicks 140-126 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton ties franchise record with 23 assists in second straight 20-20 game as Pacers beat Knicks

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 24 points, Coby White added 20 and the Chicago Bulls took advantage of NBA MVP Joel Embiid’s absence to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 105-92 on Saturday night in the opener of a home-and-home set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls take advantage of NBA MVP Joel Embiid's absence to beat 76ers, 105-92

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — LeBron James woke up sick on his 39th birthday, unsure if he'd be able to help the Los Angeles Lakers in their road game Saturday night against the Western Conference-leading Minnesota Timberwolves.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 31, Timberwolves hold on to beat the Lakers 108-106 on LeBron's 39th birthday

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 25 of his 39 points in the second half in his return to the lineup and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Golden State Warriors 132-122 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic returns to score 39 points in Mavericks' 132-122 victory over Warriors
